Alright, finally working.

In configs/transfer.py, you can set the board size and whether or not to use transfer learning.

Say we set board_size = 5 and transfer = False for the first model (we need to start with transfer = False).
Run

python transfer.py

And the model will be saved in results/5x5_save.

Now, we need to freeze the saved model weights. This converts all the variables of this model into constants.
Do this with

cd results
./freeze_graph.sh 5x5_save

This produces the results/5x5_save/frozen.pb file.

Now, we can do transfer learning.
Edit transfer.py to set board_size = 9 and transfer = True.
Then just

python transfer.py

And you are transfer learning!
